nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Proline\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets L-proline through convergent prebiotic production of shared hubs including formate, formaldehyde, hydrogen cyanide, pyruvate, and glutamate-semialdehyde equivalents, with hydrothermal carbon fixation and iron-sulfur chemistry feeding surface cyanide, sugar, and aminonitrile chemistry, followed by biochemical transamination, cyclization, and reduction to proline. Ten distinct pathways are represented as alternative routes that converge on hub intermediates and then diverge into hydrothermal, surface, and biochemical completion routes.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H6O3 (pyruvic acid/pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C4H7NO2 (2-aminobutyrate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C4H6O2 (crotonic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C5H7NO4 (glutamic acid/glutamate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H7NO2 (glutamate semialdehyde equivalent) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C5H9NO2 (L-proline) [target]\n  - mol_014: CHNO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: H3PO4 (phosphate) [starting]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Greigite-catalyzed CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Magnetite/iron reduction of CO2-derived carbon to formaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002, mol_005 -> mol_008 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from reduced carbon) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_006, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Surface photochemical generation of HCN from reduced carbon pools) [Surface]\n  - rxn_005: mol_006, mol_005 -> mol_007 (Borate-stabilized aldol formation of glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_007, mol_005, mol_015 -> mol_008 (Surface convergent pyruvate formation from glycolaldehyde and formate pools) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_008, mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_009 (Strecker-type synthesis of 2-aminobutyrate from pyruvate/cyanide network) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_009 -> mol_010 (Surface dehydration to unsaturated C4 acid) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_008, mol_010, mol_003 -> mol_011 (Biochemical-like homologation and transamination to glutamate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_010: mol_011, mol_002 -> mol_012 (Reduction of glutamate to glutamate-semialdehyde equivalent) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_012, mol_002 -> mol_013 (Cyclization and reduction to L-proline) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_004 -> mol_014 (HCN hydration to formamide as auxiliary cyanide reservoir) [Surface]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Direct hydrothermal pyruvate to proline route (5 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal C1 to HCN-assisted route (8 steps)\n  - P3: Formate-formaldehyde-glycolaldehyde surface convergence (7 steps)\n  - P4: Hydrothermal pyruvate plus surface cyanide diversification (8 steps)\n  - P5: Formamide-buffered cyanide pathway (9 steps)\n  - P6: Surface pyruvate convergence from glycolaldehyde (9 steps)\n  - P7: Dual-convergence formate and pyruvate route (8 steps)\n  - P8: HCN-first then pyruvate-assisted glutamate route (8 steps)\n  - P9: Hydrothermal-to-surface-to-biochemical closed loop (9 steps)\n  - P10: Maximum redundancy multi-hub route (10 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_005, mol_008, mol_011, mol_012\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            