nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Proline\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets proline through a chemically conservative prebiotic family centered on glutamate-semialdehyde / 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate (P5C), while avoiding poorly supported shortcuts criticized in prior attempts. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies robust C1-C3 feedstocks (formate, acetate, pyruvate, alanine) from CO2/H2 on iron-sulfur minerals. Surface chemistry supplies HCN, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde, oxaloacetate, aspartate, and glutamate via cyanosulfidic photochemistry, borate-stabilized sugar chemistry, and Strecker/transamination-like sequences under wet-dry cycling. Biochemical/prebiotic closure then converts glutamate to glutamate semialdehyde, cyclizes to P5C, and reduces to proline; stereochemical enrichment to L-proline is not assumed at the synthetic step itself but is attributed to downstream mineral or chiral-phase selection. The network is organized around hubs HCN, pyruvate, oxaloacetate, glutamate, and P5C, with multiple convergent routes from hydrothermal and surface environments into the proline family.\n\nMOLECULES (21 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetic acid/acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid/pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H4O5 (oxaloacetic acid/oxaloacetate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H7NO4 (aspartic acid/aspartate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H