ill the speculative C5 homologation and the weak conversion of pyroglutamate to P5C. Better than many alternatives, but still below approval threshold.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_013\",\n        \"rxn_017\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Prioritize this branch only if pyroglutamate-to-P5C chemistry can be experimentally supported.\",\n        \"Rebuild the C5 assembly step from aspartate/oxaloacetate with explicit intermediates.\",\n        \"Consider P5C generation via semialdehyde from a more activated glutamate derivative instead of pyroglutamate.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.86,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.34,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.74,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.38,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.78,\n        \"rxn_016\": 0.22,\n        \"rxn_018\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_019\": 0.72\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.56,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.75,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.86,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.72,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.66,\n      \"feedback\": \"Alanine-mediated transfer gives this route sensible amino-group economy, and the mixed-environment progression is strong. Nevertheless, the route still depends on an underdefined oxaloacetate formation, a speculative homologation to 2-oxoglutarate, and an especially weak glutamate-to-semialdehyde reduction. Good network design, insufficient chemical grounding in the key bottleneck zone.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_011\",\n        \"rxn_013\",\n        \"rxn_016\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Strengthen oxaloacetate synthesis with explicit intermediate chemistry.\",\n        \"Use aminonitrile or hydroxy-acid chemistry to bridge toward glutamate more plausibly.\",\n        \"Define reducing equivalents and catalysts in the final reduction sequence.\"\n   